Trenton.Nottingham High School (New Jersey):
Nottingham High School (also known as Hamilton High School North) is a four-year comprehensive public high school serving students in ninth through twelfth grades located in Hamilton Township, in Mercer County, New Jersey, United States, operating as one of the three secondary schools of the Hamilton Township School District.
As of the 2015-16 school year, the school had an enrollment of 1,366 students and 95.1 classroom teachers (on an FTE basis), for a student–teacher ratio of 14.4:1. There were 616 students (45.1% of enrollment) eligible for free lunch and 130 (9.5% of students) eligible for reduced-cost lunch.
